[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is 3 566 004, with reports of cases by 216 countries and territories worldwide. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 97.7% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA, with over 1 million confirmed cases now represents 33.3% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 248 282 deaths have been reported, 243 649 (98.1%) outside mainland China.

In descending rank order, the USA is number 1 for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and Italy is number 3, followed by the UK, France, Germany, Russia, Turkey, Brazil, and Iran as number 10. China is now number 11. The US has the highest number of newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (27 348) followed by Russia (10 633) and Brazil (4588). Russia and Brazil have both moved up their rankings in the 10 countries reporting the most number of cases globally. - Mod.MPP]

