[4] WHO situation report 104 (as of 3 May 2020)
Date: Sun 3 May 2020
Source: WHO [abridged, edited]
https://www.who.int/docs/default-source/coronaviruse/situation-reports/20200503-covid-19-sitrep-104.pdf


*The situation report includes information provided by national authorities as of 10:00 CEST, 2 May 2020
This report has been reformatted to improve accessibility for persons with visual impairment.

Highlights
----------
- WHO has recently updated the document on Country Preparedness and Response Status for COVID19 (https://www.who.int/who-documents-detail/updated-country-preparedness-and-response-status-for-covid-19-as-of-30-april-2020). The document highlighted that all countries are at risk and need to prepare for and respond to COVID-19. Each country is encouraged to plan its preparedness and response actions in line with the global Strategic Preparedness and Response Plan.

- As Yemen confirms its 1st cases of COVID-19, WHO's Regional Office for the Eastern Mediterranean issued a statement, stressing that collective action and commitment is the only way to mitigate the pandemic. "As long as even one case is unidentified and not properly treated, isolated and contacts traced, COVID-19 will continue to pose a significant threat to the Yemeni people and the country's struggling health system" (http://www.emro.who.int/media/news/statement-by-who-regional-office-for-the-eastern-mediterranean-on-covid-19-in-yemen.html).

- WHO has recently published FAQs for COVID-19 Supply Portal (https://www.who.int/who-documents-detail/covid-19-supply-portal-frequently-asked-questions). The COVID-19 Supply Portal is a purpose built tool to facilitate national authorities and all implementing partners supporting COVID-19 National Action Plans to request critical supplies.

- Since [15 Apr 2020], WHO is providing weekly updates on COVID-19, with the latest update published on 1 May [2020]. The report complements the daily situation reports, in addition to providing details on WHO funding mechanism.

